5 agencies, and statewide postsecondary education associations on
6 student financial aid policy to improve this state's administration
7 of programs.
8 (d) Collaborate with the center for educational performance
9 and information and individual colleges and universities to ensure
10 streamlined and coordinated collection of data analyzing the
11 following:
12 (i) Postsecondary education costs, including a comparison to
13 national and regional averages.
14 (ii) Student enrollment.
15 (iii) Degree completion.
