18 students, prospective students, and their families in making
19 decisions on postsecondary education.
20 (f) Coordinate with other state agencies and school districts
21 to increase utilization and awareness of postsecondary
22 opportunities, including, but not limited to, early and middle
23 college, dual enrollment, and private skills training scholarships.
24 (g) Track and provide resources to increase completion of the
25 free application for federal student aid.
